-- Wells Fargo Hires Natalie Cohen as Senior Muni Analyst in Securities Unit
-- Justin Doom
-- 2010-08-02T21:10:30Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2010-08-02/wells-fargo-hires-natalie-cohen-as-senior-muni-analyst-in-securities-unit.html

          
          
             Wells Fargo & Co. , with more than
$1.2 trillion in assets, is adding  Natalie Cohen  to the research
and economics department of its securities unit as a managing
director and senior municipal-bond analyst.  
 Cohen, who started consulting firm  National Municipal
Research Inc. , will be based in New York, Wells Fargo said today
in a statement. Cohen holds a master of public administration
degree from New York University and is a Hampshire College
graduate, the bank said. Earlier, she was a managing director
for bond insurer Financial Security Assurance, Wells Fargo said.  
 “Natalie’s extensive knowledge and experience in the
industry will significantly enhance our service capabilities,”
 Diane Schumaker-Krieg , the San Francisco-based bank’s global
head of research and economics, said in the statement.  
 Cohen has also worked for New York City’s budget office,
Moody’s Investors Service, American Capital Access and Enhance
Reinsurance/Asset Guaranty and is the author of
 thepublicpurse.com , a blog on U.S. state and local trends, the
bank said.  
